  "text": "Substitute A = L, B = D in Corollary 2 to obtain the optimal solution u 2 , . . . , u p+1 , the generalized eigenvectors of (L, D). We will show that in several aspects using these degree-normalized eigenvectors is more natural than using the eigenvectors of the Laplacian. In fact Shi and Malik [CITATION_1] have already shown that the degree-normalized eigenvectors are more suitable for the problem of image segmentation. For the visualization task, the motivation and explanation are very different.",
